com.vmware.esx.settings.depots

Interface Online

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, OnlineTypes, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    OnlineStub

    public interface Online
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, OnlineTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The Online interface provides methods to manage online software depots used during ESX lifecycle management.

        Online.ListInvocation list()
        Returns a list of currently configured online software depots.

        Invocation Result:
        Map of currently configured online software depots keyed by their identifiers. The key in the return value Map will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.esx.settings.depots.online.

        Returns:
        instance of Online.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Unauthenticated - if the caller is not authenticated.
        ServiceUnavailable - If the service is not available.
        Error - If there is some unknown internal error. The accompanying error message will give more details about the failure.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires VcIntegrity.lifecycleSettings.Read.

        Online.CreateInvocation create(OnlineTypes.CreateSpec spec)
        Adds a new online software depot to the list of currently configured online software depots.

        Invocation Result:
        Identifier of the currently configured online depot. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.esx.settings.depots.online.

        Parameters:
        spec - Depot information.
        Returns:
        instance of Online.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Unauthenticated - If the caller is not authenticated.
        InvalidArgument - If an invalid location is provided.
        AlreadyExists - If depot with given location already exists.
        Error - If there is some unknown internal error. The accompanying error message will give more details about the failure.
        ServiceUnavailable - If the service is not available.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires VcIntegrity.lifecycleSettings.Write.

      • delete

        Online.DeleteInvocation delete(java.lang.String depot)
        The task-based delete() method removes content of a user-imported online depot from vLCM completely. As a result, the URL of the user-imported online depot will also be removed. Note: 1. To remove content of system-defined online depots, use flush() method. 2. The non task-based delete() method has been deprecated. It only deletes the record of depot from the list of imported online software depots, instead of removing the depot's content from the system.
        Parameters:
        depot - Identifier of the depot to be removed. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.esx.settings.depots.online.
        Returns:
        instance of Online.DeleteInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described delete operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Unauthenticated - If the caller is not authenticated.
        InvalidArgument - If the given depot is system-defined. This error is applicable to the task-based delete() method only.
        NotFound - If there is no depot associated with parameter depot in the system.
        ResourceInUse - If the content of depot to be deleted is used in some baseline or desired state. The value of the data property of Error will be the PrecheckResult class that lists the information of affected baselines and desired states. This error is applicable to the task-based delete() method only.
        ServiceUnavailable - If the service is not available.
        Error - If there some unknown internal error. The accompanying error message will give more details about the failure. For task-based delete() method, once the task is started, it does NOT stop if encountering an error. Instead, it will continuously run to completion. In this case, the value of the data property of Error will be the DeleteResult class that lists all the errors encountered.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires VcIntegrity.lifecycleDepots.Delete.

      • flush

        Online.FlushInvocation flush(java.lang.String depot)
        The task-based flush() method removes content of a system-defined online depot from vLCM completely. As a result, the system-defined online depot will be disabled. Note: To remove content of user-imported online depots, use the task-based delete() method.
        Parameters:
        depot - Identifier of the depot to be removed. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.esx.settings.depots.online.
        Returns:
        instance of Online.FlushInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described flush operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Unauthenticated - If the caller is not authenticated.
        InvalidArgument - If the given depot is NOT system-defined.
        NotFound - If there is no depot associated with parameter depot in the system.
        ResourceInUse - If the content of depot to be deleted is used in some baseline or desired state. The value of the data property of Error will be the PrecheckResult class that lists the information of affected baselines and desired states.
        ServiceUnavailable - If the service is not available.
        Error - If there some unknown internal error. The accompanying error message will give more details about the failure. flush() is a task-based method. Once the task is started, it does NOT stop if encountering an error. Instead, it will continuously run to completion. In this case, the value of the data property of Error will be the FlushResult class that lists all the errors encountered.
